Blows on your Words the Self-admiring Sin : If unresolved to choose the Better Part , Your forward Tongue belies your languid Heart
your peaceful Mind Above Self-seeking blessed
so Mystically long , Till Certain Inspiration
no farther Motive seek , Speak or without , or with Reluctance speak : To Love's Habitual Sense by Acts aspire , And kindle , till you catch the Gospel-Fire
Speak what within his Cognisance may fall
him his own beloved Ideas back , Your Notions till they look like His
smiles to Peace confirmed and Conquest due
his Channel parts with Pain , The Lanquid loathes an Elevated Strain
at good-natured Chat , Where all , except the Love , is low and flat
With pensive Process all they hear digest : Here well-weighed Words with wary Foresight sow , For all you say will sink , and every Seed will grow
first Acquaintance press each Truth severe
they Part , If stubborn Nature long holds out the Heart
lay by its Roughness to oblige
Convictions keen , and Zeal of Prayer
love Rules ; till freed from Passion's Reign , Till blameless Moral Rectitude they gain

his Form as Suppliant by your Side , ( A helpless Worm , for whom the Saviour died ) Into his Soul call down the Eternal Beam , And longing ask to spend
